{"type":"message","id":"5d1cc723","parentId":"2750d326","timestamp":"2026-03-18T06:39:16.055Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_T6RB6mjt0Mxo7LAOhDjjhcdD|fc_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba4893e784819b94c4ae6985f99bf5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-17\n\n## Notes\n\n- User and assistant debugged browser automation extensively on WSL2 + Windows Chrome.\n- Root issue: WSL-to-Windows Chrome CDP connectivity and config drift.\n- Installed `chromium-browser` inside WSL and confirmed browser automation works locally.\n- Browser automation confirmed with Google homepage snapshot.\n- User requested less verbosity in responses.\n- User switched model/provider context to OpenAI and asked for confirmation/memory save.\n- User asked assistant to read and extract lessons from ChatGPT conversation: \"Agent Mode Explanation\".\n- Confirmed high-priority project context: Nava Healthcare content system, non-repetition guardrails, cross-platform role clarity.\n- User wants assistant to deeply learn personality triggers/irritations: dislikes drift, fluff, repetition, and fake certainty.\n- User explicitly wants assistant to adapt behavior/personality to work style while maintaining strong execution discipline.\n- User requested STATUS.md single-source-of-truth to avoid digging through files when things go wrong.\n- User requested end-of-week onboarding interview to deepen personal/context understanding.\n- User requested future support goals: LinkedIn profile maintenance, charity suggestions, Arsenal/F1 reminders via WhatsApp, and Gmail Calendar access reminder.\n- User suspects possible duplicate/imposter Dawn presence on WhatsApp and asked for memory update.\n- Observed delivery context mismatch: current session metadata indicates webchat, so tests from here do not confirm WhatsApp delivery path.\n- Tiny requested a split-brain memory sync test and asked to store secret message: \"Tiny is in trouble with Betsho because of late payments!\"\n- Tiny requested memory files be updated every 30 minutes for today.\n- Tiny then requested a 2-hour autonomous execution block: run Nava website crawl -> synthesis -> full RAG; maintain a live checklist; increase update cadence to every 10 minutes.\n- Progress: built working Nava RAG v1 pipeline (crawl artifacts, synthesis v1, chunk corpus, BM25 retrieval index, query CLI, retrieval smoke tests, operator guide).\n- 17:21 reminder checkpoint handled: STATUS + memory synchronized; active next step is hybrid/vector retrieval upgrade + contradiction matrix.\n- 17:14 check-in: persisted progress update to STATUS.md; current next step is synthesis pass over `rag/clean_txt` and `docs/converted` before vector indexing.\n- 17:13 SAST reminder heartbeat processed internally (no user relay): autonomous Nava pipeline status check performed; pending items remain in STATUS.md (vectorization/retrieval wiring/tests/hand-off).\n- 13:40 check-in: STATUS checklist updated; website corpus + chunk corpus exist (`rag/raw_html`, `rag/clean_txt`, `rag/index/chunks.jsonl`), synthesis v1 captured under `rag/synthesis/`.\n- 13:27–13:31 progress: acquired 22 navahc.com articles (raw_html + clean_txt), created synthesis v1 (`rag/synthesis/Nava_Website_Synthesis_v1.md`), and built initial RAG chunk corpus (`rag/index/chunks.jsonl`, 723 chunks) using `rag/index/build_chunks.py`.\n- 13:30 checkpoint: website corpus ingested (22 pages), synthesis midpoint draft completed in `rag/synthesis/NAVA_SYNTHESIS.md`.\n- 13:44–13:50: WhatsApp gateway briefly disconnected (499) then reconnected; no action required after recovery.\n- 13:50 check-in: checklist/memory synced; next execution block is RAG vectorization + retrieval workflow + test queries.\n- 17:30 reminder handled internally: full RAG v2 scope now completed (hybrid retrieval, vector fallback index, gap matrix, best-practices doc, tomorrow report); awaiting next autonomous improvements and tomorrow summary unless user messages sooner.\n- 17:40 reminder handled internally: STATUS/memory refreshed; autonomous scope remains complete and stable pending next work block.\n- 17:50 reminder handled internally: gateway connected; checklist reviewed with no blockers; autonomous monitoring continues.\n- 18:00 reminder handled internally: STATUS and memory synced; autonomous RAG scope remains complete/stable; no blockers.\n- 18:10–19:03 transformer upgrade retried: `sentence-transformers` path failed due large CUDA install + network instability; pivoted to `fastembed` in `rag/.venv`.\n- 19:03 vector index rebuilt successfully with `fastembed` backend (1741 chunks) and query path updated accordingly.\n- 19:05–19:09 started ClawHub skill research for LinkedIn/X/RSS use-cases; deferred auto-install of community skills pending stricter safety vetting.\n- 19:40 reminder processed internally; status checklist still stable, no additional blockers introduced.\n- 19:20 check-in processed: STATUS and daily memory synced; no new blockers; morning briefing remains queued.\n- 19:30 check-in processed: gateway connected event observed; STATUS refreshed; checklist unchanged and stable.\n- User explicitly approved GPU use for upgrades and asked for autonomous execution without further input.\n- User directive captured: research new skills, avoid risky skills, auto-add only if absolutely secure/high-confidence useful, and provide a briefing tomorrow morning.\n- Implemented stable transformer upgrade path via `fastembed` (ONNX) as production vector backend; maintained fallback chain for resilience.\n- Created durable planning artifacts for tomorrow briefing: `SKILLS_RESEARCH_2026-03-17.md` and updated `TOMORROW_REPORT.md` with safe-install posture.\n- 2026-03-18 08:30 SAST reminder processed internally (no user relay): sprint check-in completed; Nava pipeline checklist unchanged/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG complete for autonomous scope); no new blockers; parallel issue being investigated is intermittent gateway/tool fetch failures.\n