)\n\n4. `gemini` (skill) — optional bridge to custom Gem workflow\n   - Status: skill exists; binary missing\n   - Decision: add only if we actively integrate your Gemini writing loop this sprint\n\n### B) Nice-to-have\n1. `blogwatcher` (skill) — RSS/topic monitoring\n   - Status: binary missing\n   - Decision: defer (not needed for same-day queue build)\n\n2. `nano-pdf` (skill) — extraction from PDF strategy docs\n   - Decision: optional, only if source docs arrive as PDF\n\n## Immediate setup decisions (today)\n- Keep installs minimal during content-production day.\n- Prioritize workflow artifacts over tooling sprawl.\n- Use existing RAG + guardrails + manual image prompting path first.\n\n## Proposed install order (if approved)\n1) `openai-image-gen` deps/config\n2) `summarize` deps/config\n3) `gemini` deps/config (only if Google Docs/Gem integration starts today)\n4) `xurl` deps/config (only if auto-publish required)\n\n## Token-usage risk notes (for GPT budget)\nHigh token-use steps today:\n- Large-batch idea generation from many chunks\n- Multi-variant drafting (LinkedIn + X + Tiny + Yosef)\n- Iterative image brief refinement with long context\n\nBudget controls:\n- Process in small batches (5-8 ideas at a time)\n- Keep retrieval context capped (top-k + short excerpts)\n- Reuse structured templates instead of full freeform prompts\n- Store intermediate outputs in files; avoid re-sending full history\n\n## Local LLM recommendation (for your machine profile)\nGiven no GPU + 8GB-class RAM, best practical role is:\n- Local model for **structured editing/rewrites/classification**, not deep ideation\n- Keep retrieval/grounding strict to reduce hallucinations\n\nSuggested candidates (Ollama-compatible class):\n- `qwen2.5:3b-instruct` (or 1.5b if memory pressure) for fast low-cost transformations\n- `llama3.2:3b` for general rewrite support\n- Keep embeddings with `nomic-embed-text`\n\nAvoid as primary local writer on this hardware:\n- 7B+ models for heavy multi-pass drafting (too slow/ram-constrained on CPU-only)\n\n## Hallucination guardrails for local model use\n- Retrieval-only answering mode (must cite source chunk IDs/URLs)\n- Output schema enforcement (reject missing evidence fields)\n- Confidence gate: if evidence < threshold, output \"insufficient support\"\n- Domain gate: reject non-Nava-staffing topics\n- Human review required before publish\n\n## Status\n- Task 1 started\n- Research file created\n- Awaiting approval to install any extra dependencies\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SKILLS_SETUP_TODAY.md\",\"content\":\"# Skills/Tools Setup — Task 1 (2026-03-18)\\n\\n## Goal\\nSelect and set up only the tools needed for Nava content operations (research -> ideas -> drafting -> images -> queue prep), with a safety-first posture.\\n\\n## Environment Snapshot\\n- GPU: none detected in WSL (`NO_NVIDIA_GPU`)\\n- CPU: Intel i7-9750H (6C/12T)\\n- RAM: 7.6 GiB\\n- Local LLM runtime: `ollama` installed\\n- Existing Ollama models:\\n  - `nomic-embed-text` (local)\\n  - `minimax-m2.5:cloud` (cloud)\\n  - `kimi-k2.5:cloud` (cloud)\\n  - `glm-5:cloud` (cloud)\\n\\n## Task-fit skill shortlist\\n\\n### A) Must-have now\\n1. `summarize` (skill) — long-source condensation for briefs\\n   - Status: skill exists; likely binary dependency missing\\n   - Decision: Enable if dependency install is clean and low-risk\\n\\n2. `openai-image-gen` (skill) — image concept generation/iteration\\n   - Status: skill exists; CLI binary missing locally\\n   - Decision: Add once API/auth path confirmed\\n\\n3. `xurl` (skill) — X/Twitter workflow support\\n   - Status: skill exists; binary missing\\n   - Decision: defer until posting path is needed (today can still draft without publish automation)\\n\\n4. `gemini` (skill) — optional bridge to custom Gem workflow\\n   - Status: skill exists; binary missing\\n   - Decision: add only if we actively integrate your Gemini writing loop this sprint\\n\\n### B) Nice-to-have\\n1. `blogwatcher` (skill) — RSS/topic monitoring\\n   - Status: binary missing\\n   - Decision: defer (not needed for same-day queue build)\\n\\n2. `nano-pdf` (skill) — extraction from PDF strategy docs\\n   - Decision: optional, only if source docs arrive as PDF\\n\\n## Immediate setup decisions (today)\\n- Keep installs minimal during content-production day.\\n- Prioritize workflow artifacts over tooling sprawl.\\n- Use existing RAG + guardrails + manual image prompting path first.\\n\\n## Proposed install order (if approved)\\n1) `openai-image-gen` deps/config\\n2) `summarize` deps/config\\n3) `gemini` deps/config (only if Google Docs/Gem integration starts today)\\n4) `xurl` deps/config (only if auto-publish required)\\n\\n## Token-usage risk notes (for GPT budget)\\nHigh token-use steps today:\\n- Large-batch idea generation from many chunks\\n- Multi-variant drafting (LinkedIn + X + Tiny + Yosef)\\n- Iterative image brief refinement with long context\\n\\nBudget controls:\\n- Process in small batches (5-8 ideas at a time)\\n- Keep retrieval context capped (top-k + short excerpts)\\n- Reuse structured templates instead of full freeform prompts\\n- Store intermediate outputs in files; avoid re-sending full history\\n\\n## Local LLM recommendation (for your machine profile)\\nGiven no GPU + 8GB-class RAM, best practical role is:\\n- Local model for **structured editing/rewrites/classification**, not deep ideation\\n- Keep retrieval/grounding strict to reduce hallucinations\\n\\nSuggested candidates (Ollama-compatible class):\\n- `qwen2.5:3b-instruct` (or 1.5b if memory pressure) for fast low-cost transformations\\n- `llama3.2:3b` for general rewrite support\\n- Keep embeddings with `nomic-embed-text`\\n\\nAvoid as primary local writer on this hardware:\\n- 7B+ models for heavy multi-pass drafting (too slow/ram-constrained on CPU-only)\\n\\n## Hallucination guardrails for local model use\\n- Retrieval-only answering mode (must cite source chunk IDs/URLs)\\n- Output schema enforcement (reject missing evidence fields)\\n- Confidence gate: if evidence < threshold, output \\\"insufficient support\\\"\\n- Domain gate: reject non-Nava-staffing topics\\n- Human review required before publish\\n\\n## Status\\n- Task 1 started\\n- Research file created\\n- Awaiting approval to install any extra dependencies\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":274,"output":1172,"cacheRead":32256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33702,"cost":{"input":0.0004795,"output":0.016408,"cacheRead":0.0056448,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.022532299999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773818057762}}
