local LLM for your role (not general use):**  \nGiven your machine profile (no NVIDIA GPU, ~8GB RAM), use local models for **tight transformation tasks**, not full creative heavy lifting.\n\nRecommended:\n- `qwen2.5:3b-instruct` (primary)\n- fallback `llama3.2:3b`\n- keep `nomic-embed-text` for embeddings\n\nUse it for:\n- rewrite/compression\n- style normalization\n- schema filling/classification\n- critique passes with strict evidence inputs\n\nNot ideal locally:\n- long-form ideation + multi-pass generation at 7B+ (too costly/slow on CPU-only).\n\n---\n\nIf you want, next in Task 1 I’ll do the **practical setup pass**:\n- check/install only the minimum deps for `summarize` + `openai-image-gen`,\n- skip `xurl`/`gemini` for now unless you want immediate integration today.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba50fdb540819ba376ba80e16de87a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":202,"output":364,"cacheRead":33664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34230,"cost":{"input":0.0003535,"output":0.005096,"cacheRead":0.0058912,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011340699999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773818105462}}
