automatically and warn before high-token GPT steps.\n\n---\n\n### Hallucination guardrails (for local model)\n- RAG-only evidence mode (must cite chunk/source)\n- reject output if no evidence field\n- domain gate (Nava staffing only)\n- confidence gate (`insufficient support` when weak)\n- human approval before publish\n\n---\n\nIf you run `wsl --shutdown` now and come back, I’ll immediately:\n1) re-check visible RAM/GPU from runtime,  \n2) set the best local model shortlist for your exact detected resources, and  \n3) continue Task 1 with the local-first setup plan.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba52835870819bbfa3ea6d0129536c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":216,"output":673,"cacheRead":41216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42105,"cost":{"input":0.00037799999999999997,"output":0.009422,"cacheRead":0.007212799999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017012799999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773818492282}}
