PDATA\\Ollama\\models\" -Recurse | Measure-Object -Property Length -Sum\n```\n\n### In WSL (if Linux-side Ollama was used)\n```bash\n~/.ollama/models\n```\n\n---\n\n### Important behavior\nOllama usually **reuses blob chunks** if they already exist, but sometimes progress looks like restart in UI/CLI even when cache exists.\n\n### Safe cleanup (only if needed)\nAfter download stabilizes, run:\n```bash\nollama list\nollama ps\n```\nThen remove only models you don’t want:\n```bash\nollama rm <model-tag>\n```\nAvoid manually deleting blobs unless you must — can corrupt cache consistency.\n\nIf you want, send me output of:\n```bash\nollama list\n```\nand I’ll tell you exactly what’s present vs partial.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba5f04bf40819bb03a6ad99fbd4498\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":212,"output":333,"cacheRead":46080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46625,"cost":{"input":0.000371,"output":0.004662,"cacheRead":0.008064,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013097000000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773821692952}}
