{"type":"message","id":"162ab611","parentId":"b54e07ee","timestamp":"2026-03-18T08:36:52.631Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Possible, yes. Common triggers:\n\n- Closing/restarting Ollama GUI while download active\n- Stopping/restarting Ollama service/app\n- Running a second pull for same model in another terminal\n- Sleep/hibernate/network drop during pull\n- Clicking a cancel/retry icon in GUI (sometimes subtle)\n- Launching `ollama run <model>` before pull fully completes (can re-trigger fetch flow)\n\nSo it may not be “your fault” — often it’s service/network interruption behavior.\n\nSafe rule now:\n- one download at a time\n- keep GUI state stable (or close it and use one terminal only)\n- don’t run `ollama run` until `ollama pull` finishes 100% and model appears in `ollama list`.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba64203298819ba839888638ab4b72\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":195,"output":164,"cacheRead":47232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47591,"cost":{"input":0.00034125,"output":0.002296,"cacheRead":0.0082656,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010902849999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773823001005}}
