 handled internally: STATUS/memory refreshed; autonomous scope remains complete and stable pending next work block.\n- 17:50 reminder handled internally: gateway connected; checklist reviewed with no blockers; autonomous monitoring continues.\n- 18:00 reminder handled internally: STATUS and memory synced; autonomous RAG scope remains complete/stable; no blockers.\n- 18:10–19:03 transformer upgrade retried: `sentence-transformers` path failed due large CUDA install + network instability; pivoted to `fastembed` in `rag/.venv`.\n- 19:03 vector index rebuilt successfully with `fastembed` backend (1741 chunks) and query path updated accordingly.\n- 19:05–19:09 started ClawHub skill research for LinkedIn/X/RSS use-cases; deferred auto-install of community skills pending stricter safety vetting.\n- 19:40 reminder processed internally; status checklist still stable, no additional blockers introduced.\n- 19:20 check-in processed: STATUS and daily memory synced; no new blockers; morning briefing remains queued.\n- 19:30 check-in processed: gateway connected event observed; STATUS refreshed; checklist unchanged and stable.\n- User explicitly approved GPU use for upgrades and asked for autonomous execution without further input.\n- User directive captured: research new skills, avoid risky skills, auto-add only if absolutely secure/high-confidence useful, and provide a briefing tomorrow morning.\n- Implemented stable transformer upgrade path via `fastembed` (ONNX) as production vector backend; maintained fallback chain for resilience.\n- Created durable planning artifacts for tomorrow briefing: `SKILLS_RESEARCH_2026-03-17.md` and updated `TOMORROW_REPORT.md` with safe-install posture.\n- 2026-03-18 08:30 SAST reminder processed internally (no user relay): sprint check-in completed; Nava pipeline checklist unchanged/stable (crawl → synthesis → full RAG complete for autonomous scope); no new blockers; parallel issue being investigated is intermittent gateway/tool fetch failures.\n- 2026-03-18 08:40 SAST reminder processed internally (no user relay): sprint checklist revalidated; STATUS updated and memory synced; Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG remains complete/stable for current scope; no new blockers.\n- 2026-03-18 08:50 SAST reminder processed internally (no user relay): sprint checklist remains complete/stable for Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG; STATUS and daily memory synchronized; no new delivery blockers; intermittent fetch-failure diagnostics continue as separate infra issue.\n- 2026-03-18 09:00 SAST reminder processed internally (no user relay): sprint checklist revalidated as complete/stable; user approved hard guardrails for Nava-domain-only idea generation with mandatory source evidence/taxonomy mapping; next build phase is the content-engine layer (idea schema, scoring, channel/persona formatting, image refinement workflow, and ingest-on-publish updates for new Nava articles).\n- 2026-03-18 09:30 SAST reminder processed internally (no user relay): core Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG remains complete/stable; user requested rollback from 10-minute to 30-minute check cadence; WhatsApp cron noise disabled; Task 1 skills/tooling setup active; WSL resource exposure increased (~11 GiB RAM, 10 vCPU), `/dev/dxg` present, Windows Ollama endpoint reachable; user preference clarified to local-LLM-first execution with selective ChatGPT escalation.\n- 2026-03-18 10:00 SAST reminder processed internally (no user relay): sprint checklist unchanged (crawl → synthesis → full RAG complete/stable, no delivery blockers); Task 1 ongoing with local-model onboarding (`qwen3:4b-instruct` downloading), CLI confirmed (`ollama 0.18.0`), and interim routing policy set to local-first with guarded GPT escalation for high-reasoning tasks.\n- 2026-03-18 10:30 SAST reminder processed internally (no user relay): sprint checklist revalidated as complete/stable for Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG; no new delivery blockers; user completed WSL restart and re