U6SOt_KwR7jbJXa5qHo8Xs0HKJKitnqPOob4pY9Ct7Pfz3SViYubJQhunFxnSuQUL3KlNxqpQWHbm6ez-1CzjUaArlCKDFhG9rX0ihTNaZ3bDyEfgQCdyW4T1ApWgFWtyOUb0xFlIkrkEz9F2ue_oHtsZoJvp5VlACwBr2BMlSXwYPATietXGN3UkSGqMGn7Xgd2comc5PR_z8XGjYFG72bmOZXiHMh3_tS34QuyiwkOInFG1m4ylPqtxYP9Cqn9jOumipbHuxjKwTZkzSI-LhBejMeQa74t33alHtsd49ctEN20q02ScKTE5MdNVCZxW01Uo3h41VqbF1EpCucGfPCRaciq-RTZH0V_L3tmT6_UrNUOEE8ApuUWMZ9h9rBeDuWIHSUywiHMoO4EhrPHshnliYFje5-g4n2CJrHh4_tGC90DrAbTV40mv5xqs0PRIA66wrWyDdNxzUf4ofsPEYANipWmmr25NnhvfAUHLZMLnwKXvpWbbM7VU8jh3dcrFvjQcFTw2eCLV3v748TK1fZhn4CKr_EVAiw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating Ollama fallback guide**\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fMUa60xAhCDsFURHqxNpZMYR|fc_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba6cf2cec8819ba15e5d5241c6d917","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/OLLAMA_OPENAI_FALLBACK_GUIDE.md","content":"# OpenClaw Local-First Setup Guide (Ollama + OpenAI Fallback)\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-18_\n\n## Goal\nRun OpenClaw with:\n1) **Local Ollama model by default** for routine tasks\n2) **OpenAI fallback** when local is unavailable or a task needs higher reasoning quality\n\n---\n\n## Quick answer: should you close the running LLM now?\nIf you're waiting and not actively testing, **yes** — stop it to free RAM.\n\nCheck running models:\n```bash\nollama ps\n```\n\nStop a running model (example):\n```bash\nollama stop qwen3:4b-instruct\n```\n\nIf multiple are loaded, stop each listed model.\n\n---\n\n## Baseline prerequisites\n- Ollama installed and working on Windows\n- Model installed (current: `qwen3:4b-instruct`)\n- OpenClaw can reach Ollama API (`http://127.0.0.1:11434`)\n- OpenAI auth configured in OpenClaw (already true in this environment)\n\n---\n\n## Recommended routing policy\n\n### Use local Ollama by default for:\n- rewriting / compression\n- structured JSON outputs\n- style normalization\n- first-pass critique\n- batch formatting tasks\n\n### Escalate to OpenAI for:\n- hard reasoning / strategy tradeoffs\n- ambiguous constraints\n- final high-stakes publish polish\n- cases where local output fails guardrails\n\n---\n\n## Guardrails to reduce hallucinations\n- Require evidence fields for content outputs (URL/chunk IDs)\n- Reject out-of-domain ideas (Nava staffing/recruiting taxonomy only)\n- Force schema output for automation steps\n- If evidence weak/missing -> return `insufficient_support`\n- Human approval before publish\n\n---\n\n## Operational fallback behavior (important)\nOpenClaw does not always auto-probe local service health before every turn by default.\n\nSo use one of these patterns:\n\n### Pattern A (simple/manual)\n- Keep default model as OpenAI in OpenClaw\n- Explicitly use local model for local-suitable tasks via workflow routing discipline\n\n### Pattern B (preferred scripted switch)\nUse a tiny preflight script:\n1) check Ollama reachability\n2) if reachable -> set OpenClaw model to local alias\n3) else -> set OpenClaw model to OpenAI fallback\n\nExample (PowerShell):\n```powershell\ntry {\n  $r = Invoke-WebRequest -UseBasicParsing http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags -TimeoutSec 2\n  if ($r.StatusCode -eq 200) {\n    openclaw models set ollama/qwen3:4b-instruct\n  } else {\n    openclaw models set openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex\n  }\n}\ncatch {\n  openclaw models set openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex\n}\n```\n\n> Note: exact OpenClaw model IDs/aliases for Ollama can vary by install. Validate with:\n```bash\nopenclaw models list --all --plain\n```\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### 1) Ollama download restarts\n- Keep one download at a time\n- Avoid restarting GUI/service mid-download\n- Use stable network\n- Check cached blobs in:\n  - `%LOCALAPPDATA%\\Ollama\\models`\n  - `%USERPROFILE%\\.ollama\\models`\n\n### 2) Laptop feels slow\n- Stop idle models (`ollama ps` + `ollama stop ...`)\n- Keep one model loaded\n- Reduce context size / prompt size\n\n### 3) OpenClaw not using expected model\n- Check current session model:\n```bash\nopenclaw models status --plain\n```\n- Re-set default model:\n```bash\nopenclaw models set <model-id>\n```\n\n### 4) WSL shows less RAM than host\n- Configure `.wslconfig` memory/processors\n- Run `wsl --shutdown`\n- Reopen WSL and verify with `free -h`\n\n---\n\n## Verification checklist\n- [ ] `ollama run qwen3:4b-instruct` works\n- [ ] JSON discipline test passes\n- [ ] `openclaw models status --plain` shows intended model\n- [ ] Fallback script switches correctly when Ollama is stopped\n\n---\n\n## Current recommendation for this project\n- Keep `qwen3:4b-instruct` as local default for routine transforms\n- Use OpenAI fallback for high-reasoning/high-stakes passes\n- Apply domain/evidence/schema guardrails on all content-generation steps\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/OLLAMA_OPENAI_FALLBACK_GUIDE.md\",\"content\":\"# OpenClaw Local-First Setup Guide (Ollama + OpenAI Fallback)\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-18_\\n\\n## Goal\\nRun OpenClaw with:\\n1) **Local Ollama model by default** for routine tasks\\n2) **OpenAI fallback** when local is unavailable or a task needs higher reasoning quality\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Quick answer: should you close the running LLM now?\\nIf you're waiting and not actively testing, **yes** — stop it to free RAM.\\n\\nCheck running models:\\n```bash\\nollama ps\\n```\\n\\nStop a running model (example):\\n```bash\\nollama stop qwen3:4b-instruct\\n```\\n\\nIf multiple are loaded, stop each listed model.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Baseline prerequisites\\n- Ollama installed and working on Windows\\n- Model installed (current: `qwen3:4b-instruct`)\\n- OpenClaw can reach Ollama API (`http://127.0.0.1:11434`)\\n- OpenAI auth configured in OpenClaw (already true in this environment)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Recommended routing policy\\n\\n### Use local Ollama by default for:\\n- rewriting / compression\\n- structured JSON outputs\\n- style normalization\\n- first-pass critique\\n- batch formatting tasks\\n\\n### Escalate to OpenAI for:\\n- hard reasoning / strategy tradeoffs\\n- ambiguous constraints\\n- final high-stakes publish polish\\n- cases where local output fails guardrails\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Guardrails to reduce hallucinations\\n- Require evidence fields for content outputs (URL/chunk IDs)\\n- Reject out-of-domain ideas (Nava staffing/recruiting taxonomy only)\\n- Force schema output for automation steps\\n- If evidence weak/missing -> return `insufficient_support`\\n- Human approval before publish\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Operational fallback behavior (important)\\nOpenClaw does not always auto-probe local service health before every turn by default.\\n\\nSo use one of these patterns:\\n\\n### Pattern A (simple/manual)\\n- Keep default model as OpenAI in OpenClaw\\n- Explicitly use local model for local-suitable tasks via workflow routing discipline\\n\\n### Pattern B (preferred scripted switch)\\nUse a tiny preflight script:\\n1) check Ollama reachability\\n2) if reachable -> set OpenClaw model to local alias\\n3) else -> set OpenClaw model to OpenAI fallback\\n\\nExample (PowerShell):\\n```powershell\\ntry {\\n  $r = Invoke-WebRequest -UseBasicParsing http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags -TimeoutSec 2\\n  if ($r.StatusCode -eq 200) {\\n    openclaw models set ollama/qwen3:4b-instruct\\n  } else {\\n    openclaw models set openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex\\n  }\\n}\\ncatch {\\n  openclaw models set openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex\\n}\\n```\\n\\n> Note: exact OpenClaw model IDs/aliases for Ollama can vary by install. Validate with:\\n```bash\\nopenclaw models list --all --plain\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Troubleshooting\\n\\n### 1) Ollama download restarts\\n- Keep one download at a time\\n- Avoid restarting GUI/service mid-download\\n- Use stable network\\n- Check cached blobs in:\\n  - `%LOCALAPPDATA%\\\\Ollama\\\\models`\\n  - `%USERPROFILE%\\\\.ollama\\\\models`\\n\\n### 2) Laptop feels slow\\n- Stop idle models (`ollama ps` + `ollama stop ...`)\\n- Keep one model loaded\\n- Reduce context size / prompt size\\n\\n### 3) OpenClaw not using expected model\\n- Check current session model:\\n```bash\\nopenclaw models status --plain\\n```\\n- Re-set default model:\\n```bash\\nopenclaw models set <model-id>\\n```\\n\\n### 4) WSL shows less RAM than host\\n- Configure `.wslconfig` memory/processors\\n- Run `wsl --shutdown`\\n- Reopen WSL and verify with `free -h`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Verification checklist\\n- [ ] `ollama run qwen3:4b-instruct` works\\n- [ ] JSON discipline test passes\\n- [ ] `openclaw models status --plain` shows intended model\\n- [ ] Fallback script switches correctly when Ollama is stopped\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current recommendation for this project\\n- Keep `qwen3:4b-instruct` as local default for routine transforms\\n- Use OpenAI fallback for high-reasoning/high-stakes passes\\n- Apply domain/evidence/schema guardrails on all content-generation steps\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":311,"output":1308,"cacheRead":65152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66771,"cost":{"input":0.00054425,"output":0.018312,"cacheRead":0.0114016,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.030257849999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773825258095}}
