{"type":"message","id":"9cda48e9","parentId":"7e47f2e2","timestamp":"2026-03-18T09:15:00.745Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Great questions.\n\n1) **Should you close the LLM running in background?**  \nYes — if you’re waiting, close it to free RAM.\n\nUse:\n```bash\nollama ps\nollama stop qwen3:4b-instruct\n```\n\n2) **Can I create a setup/troubleshooting guide?**  \nDone. I created and committed:\n\n- `OLLAMA_OPENAI_FALLBACK_GUIDE.md`\n\nIt covers:\n- local-first routing\n- OpenAI fallback\n- guardrails against hallucinations\n- troubleshooting download/restarts/perf\n- verification checklist\n\n3) **Will setup auto-check Ollama and fall back to ChatGPT if down?**  \nIt can, but not magically by default every turn unless we enforce it.  \nIn the guide I included a **preflight switch script** pattern that:\n- checks Ollama health\n- uses local model if available\n- otherwise switches to OpenAI fallback\n\nIf you want, next I’ll implement that preflight as an actual script in this workspace so you can run one command.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba6d0e3480819b9ab77a1443467ef0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":897,"output":227,"cacheRead":66048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67172,"cost":{"input":0.00156975,"output":0.003178,"cacheRead":0.0115584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01630615}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773825291213}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ea1e04d","parentId":"9cda48e9","timestamp":"2026-03-18T09:16:55.418Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-03-18 11:16 GMT+2] Yes please. And tell me where I can find this guide? Additionally, before I close Qwen, if it is not stressing my RAM at all (I guess because it is idle) do I need to close it? Is it better for you if I close it?"}],"timestamp":1773825415405}}
