{"type":"message","id":"717eb25a","parentId":"05eb4231","timestamp":"2026-03-18T09:34:28.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] A distro = a Linux installation inside WSL.\n\nExample names:\n- `Ubuntu`\n- `Ubuntu-22.04`\n- `Debian`\n- `kali-linux`\n\nSo when I say “WSL distro name,” I just mean:  \n**which Linux environment should Windows run commands inside**.\n\nYou can see yours with:\n```powershell\nwsl -l -q\n```\nThen we use that exact name in commands if needed.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba71a2dfec819bacd5defb9d6354d0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":1091,"output":101,"cacheRead":69376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70568,"cost":{"input":0.00190925,"output":0.001414,"cacheRead":0.0121408,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01546405}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773826462350}}
