{"type":"compaction","id":"f8e95f2d","parentId":"2391b8f9","timestamp":"2026-03-18T10:53:52.121Z","summary":"## Decisions\n- **Local-first LLM strategy**: Default to local Ollama for routine content tasks (summarization, rewrite, formatting, schema filling), escalate to ChatGPT only for hard reasoning, ambiguous strategy, or high-stakes final drafting\n- **Qwen3:4b-instruct selected**: Best balance of quality/speed for 16GB laptop, ~2.5-4.5GB download size, 4-8GB RAM runtime\n- **Guardrails enforced**: RAG-only evidence mode, domain gate (Nava staffing/recruiting only), confidence gate (\"insufficient support\" when weak), human approval before publish\n- **WSL memory boost applied**: Increased WSL visible RAM from ~7.6GB to ~11GB via .wslconfig updates\n- **Skill install deferral**: Keep installs minimal during content-production day; prioritize workflow artifacts over tooling sprawl\n\n## Open TODOs\n1. Complete Task 1: Skill/tool research + setup (70% done) - finalize install/skip/defer list\n2. Verify Qwen3:4b-instruct works locally (download in progress, currently failing/restarting repeatedly)\n3. Lock exact local model routing policy after benchmark test\n4. Task 2: Content engine spec finalization (45-60 min)\n5. Task 3: Ingestion update flow for new articles (45-75 min)\n6. Task 4: Generate idea bank from corpus (90-120 min)\n7. Task 5: Draft queue-ready posts for LinkedIn/X/FB (120-180 min)\n8. Task 6: Image refinement workflow (90-150 min)\n9. Task 7: Final queue pack + ordering (30-45 min)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Quality over speed: \"I don't want guaranteed delivery, I want this done properly\"\n- Must warn before any high-token GPT steps\n- Must map every idea to Nava staffing/recruiting taxonomy with source evidence URLs\n- Must reject non-Nava-domain content\n- Human review required before any publish\n- Single model loaded at a time to avoid RAM pressure\n- Close heavy apps (Chrome tabs) during local LLM inference\n\n## Pending user asks\n1. **Qwen download issue**: Download keeps restarting from scratch - user suspects GUI closure triggered it, needs to verify completion\n2. **Model reliability test**: User still needs to run the rewrite test and JSON strict format test\n3. **Local model benchmarking**: Need latency, quality, and RAM usage results from user after Qwen completes\n4. **Google Docs + Gemini integration**: User wants to integrate with their custom Gem for writing style transfer - deferred to later phase\n5. **Image refinement process**: User asked about refining AI-generated images - workflow defined but not yet built\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- Cron job (WhatsApp check, now disabled): `a17613ed-5c6e-46a8-aff9-d010ceb706b0`\n- Cron job (sprint check-in, 30min): `fe4180d9-037f-413a-a1dd-c7291e5d2729`\n- WSL config paths: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/.wslconfig`, `/mnt/c/Users/LENOVO P53/.wslconfig`\n- Memory file (yesterday): `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-17.md`\n- Guardrails file: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/config/content_guardrails.yaml`\n- Task 1 setup doc: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SKILLS_SETUP_TODAY.md`\n- Ollama endpoint: `http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags`\n- Existing Ollama models: `nomic-embed-text:latest`, `minimax-m2.5:cloud`, `kimi-k2.5:cloud`, `glm-5:cloud`\n- Qwen model being downloaded: `qwen3:4b-instruct` (exact tag pending verification)\n- Current time context: Wednesday, March 18th, 2026 — ~10:36 AM (Africa/Johannesburg)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Goal\n- Connect the AI assistant to a local LLM for improved performance/reduced latency\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User reported laptop latency is acceptable (1-2 seconds)\n- User asking what actions needed to complete local LLM connection\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Ran `openclaw models set --help` to understand model configuration\n- [x] Ran `openclaw models list --all --plain` to see available models\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Determining steps to connect to local LLM\n\n### Blocked\n- [None explicitly stated - awaiting user guidance on connection method]\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **None yet made** - conversation was interrupted for context extraction\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Await user response on what connection method to use for local LLM\n2. Complete model configuration once connection method is determined\n\n## Critical Context\n- Using OpenClaw tool (version 2026.3.8)\n- Available models include various Amazon Bedrock models (Claude, Nova, Titan, etc.) and DeepSeek models\n- Tool path: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace`\n\n---\n\n## Decisions\n- None yet made in this conversation segment\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Connect assistant to local LLM (user's stated goal)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Latency requirement: acceptable at 1-2 seconds\n\n## Pending user asks\n- \"What do I now have to do to connect you to the local LLM? Do I wait for you to complete your tasks?\"\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- **Label**: \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\"\n- **ID**: \"gateway-client\"\n- **Name**: \"openclaw-tui\"\n- **Username**: \"openclaw-tui\"\n- **Date/Time**: Wed 2026-03-18 11:08 GMT+2\n- **Tool commands**: `openclaw models set --help`, `openclaw models list --all --plain`\n- **Working directory**: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace`\n- **OpenClaw version**: 2026.3.8 (3caab92)\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: System: [2026-03-18 11:00:00 GMT+2] Reminder: 30-minute sprint check-in. Update checklist/progress for Nava website crawl -> synthesis -> full RAG, and persist key memory notes in memory/2026-03-17.md (and MEMORY.md only if long-term-worthy).\n\nA scheduled reminder has been triggered. The reminder content is:\n\nReminder: 30-minute sprint check-in. Update checklist/progress for Nava website crawl -> synthesis -> full RAG, and persist key memory notes in memory/2026-03-17.md (and MEMORY.md only if long-term-worthy).\n\nHandle this reminder internally. Do not relay it to the user unless explicitly re...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall x3]\n- Tool result (exec): SKILLS_RESEARCH_2026-03-17.md\nSKILLS_SETUP_TODAY.md\nSTATUS.md\nTOMORROW_REPORT.md\nmemory\n- Tool result (read): # STATUS — Nava Website Synthesis + Full RAG\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-18 10:30 SAST_\n\n## Mission\nBuild a usable Nava \"mind\" by combining:\n1) website articles (crawl + synthesis)\n2) provided docs in `docs/` and `docs/converted/`\n3) full RAG index + testable query workflow\n\n## Checklist\n\n### 0) Coordination / Ops\n- [x] Persist memory notes for this autonomous block\n- [x] Sprint check cadence adjusted and reverted to every 30 minutes per user request\n- [x] Create live status checklist file\n\n### 1) Website Corpus Acquisition\n- [x] Identify target domain(s) (`navahc.com`; explicitly exclude `navacen...\n- Tool result (read): # 2026-03-17\n\n## Notes\n\n- User and assistant debugged browser automation extensively on WSL2 + Windows Chrome.\n- Root issue: WSL-to-Windows Chrome CDP connectivity and config drift.\n- Installed `chromium-browser` inside WSL and confirmed browser automation works locally.\n- Browser automation confirmed with Google homepage snapshot.\n- User requested less verbosity in responses.\n- User switched model/provider context to OpenAI and asked for confirmation/memory save.\n- User asked assistant to read and extract lessons from ChatGPT conversation: \"Agent Mode Explanation\".\n- Confirmed high-priority p...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/STATUS.md.\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-17.md.\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): {\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\"\n}\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): # MEMORY.md - Long-term Memory\n\n## About the User\n\n- **Name:** Tiny\n- Running OpenClaw on WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)\n- Gateway token: \"ollama\" (short - security warning)\n- Connected WhatsApp channel (+2776...)\n- Uses Hacker News\n\n## Preferences & Notes\n\n- Prefers concise responses; asked assistant to be less verbose.\n- Dislikes AI drift, recycled ideas, and over-verbosity; values precision and directness.\n- Wants pushback over agreeability during concept development.\n- Strong preference for concept pressure-testing before drafting.\n- LinkedIn workflow preference: concept discussion -> d...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): [master 599a55a] Internal 11:00 check-in: sync STATUS and memory for Task 1 local-LLM onboarding\n 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+)\n- Assistant: NO_REPLY\n[non-text content: thinking]\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-03-18 11:03 GMT+2] I have installed Qwen, here is the first test: PS C:\\WINDOWS\\system32> ollama run qwen3:4b-instruct\n>>> Rewrite in a concise executive tone: Reactive hiring is expensive because vacancies and bad fit turnover create hidden downstream costs.\nReactive hiring incurs hidden costs from vacancies and poor fit turnover.\n- Assistant: [[reply_to_current]] Nice — that output is good.  \nIt’s concise, accurate, and followed instruction cleanly.\n\nNext, run the **JSON reliability test**:\n\n```bash\nollama run qwen3:4b-instruct \"Return strict JSON only: {\\\"topic\\\":\\\"healthcare staffing\\\",\\\"claim\\\":\\\"Reactive hiring increases total cost\\\",\\\"risk\\\":\\\"turnover and vacancy drag margins\\\"}\"\n```\n\nThen send me:\n1) exact output  \n2) rough latency  \n3) whether laptop felt sluggish\n\nIf this passes, I’ll lock Qwen 4B as your local default for Task 1 routing.\n[non-text content: thinking]\n- User: System: [2026-03-18 11:06:34 GMT+2] WhatsApp gateway connected.\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-03-18 11:07 GMT+2] PS C:\\WINDOWS\\system32> ollama run qwen3:4b-instruct\n>>> Rewrite in a concise executive tone: Reactive hiring is expensive because vacancies and bad fit turnover create hidden downstream costs.\nReactive hiring incurs hidden costs from vacancies and poor fit turnover.\n\n>>> Return strict JSON only: {\\\"topic\"\\:\\\"healthcare staffing\\\",\\\"...\n- Assistant: [[reply_to_current]] Perfect — that passed.\n\n- ✅ Instruction following: good  \n- ✅ Strict JSON compliance: good  \n- ✅ Output quality for structured tasks: good enough to proceed\n\nSo I’m locking **`qwen3:4b-instruct` as local default** for now.\n\nOne last calibration from you (quick):\n1) Approx latency (e.g., 2s / 8s / 20s)?  \n2) Did your laptop feel laggy during generation?\n\nThen I’ll finalize Task 1 with the production routing policy:\n- local tasks vs GPT escalation triggers\n- hard guardrails for hallucination control\n- tool install/skip/defer list.\n[non-text content: thinking]\n\n<read-files>\n/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SKILLS_RESEARCH_2026-03-17.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/docs/Nava_Blog_Research_Notes.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-18.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/synthesis/Nava_Website_Synthesis_v1.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SKILLS_SETUP_TODAY.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/STATUS.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-17.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/config/content_guardrails.yaml\n/mnt/c/Users/LENOVO P53/.wslconfig\n/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/.wslconfig\n</modified-files>\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"53669d97","tokensBefore":81642,"details":{"readFiles":["/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SKILLS_RESEARCH_2026-03-17.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/docs/Nava_Blog_Research_Notes.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-18.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/synthesis/Nava_Website_Synthesis_v1.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SKILLS_SETUP_TODAY.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/STATUS.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-17.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/config/content_guardrails.yaml","/mnt/c/Users/LENOVO P53/.wslconfig","/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/.wslconfig"]},"fromHook":true}
