3DGS-IsBVEbj4vg8anVaQww\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Recommending smaller models and commands**\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Yep — totally fair. Let’s remove Qwen cleanly.\n\n### Remove Qwen (PowerShell)\n```powershell\nollama ps\nollama stop qwen3:4b-instruct\nollama rm qwen3:4b-instruct\nollama list\n```\n\nThat will:\n- stop it if loaded\n- delete local model files\n- confirm it’s gone\n\n---\n\n### Should you try a smaller model?\n**Yes**, for your laptop this is the right move.  \nYou’ll trade some quality for much better speed + lower RAM.\n\nGood next candidates:\n- `qwen2.5:1.5b` (very light, fast, weaker reasoning)\n- `llama3.2:3b` (better balance, still much lighter than Qwen 4B)\n- `phi3:mini` (compact, decent structured output)\n\nIf you want one default pick: **`llama3.2:3b`** first.\n\n---\n\n### Quick test flow (2 mins)\n```powershell\nollama pull llama3.2:3b\nollama run llama3.2:3b \"Return strict JSON only: {\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"model\\\":\\\"test\\\"}\"\n```\n\nIf it feels good, we point OpenClaw to it.  \nIf not, we drop to `qwen2.5:1.5b`.\n\nIf you want, I’ll give you the exact single command to switch OpenClaw once you pick the model.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba92206c3c819b940240cee01e0aa7\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":280,"output":456,"cacheRead":38144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38880,"cost":{"input":0.00049,"output":0.006384,"cacheRead":0.0066752,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0135492}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773834772176}}
