 and usually better behaved on RAM/latency in agent workflows.  \nFor your use case (rewrite + JSON + structured tasks), it can be effective.\n\nI’d test it head-to-head with `llama3.2:3b` because Llama often has better ecosystem stability.\n\n### Do this quick bake-off (PowerShell)\n```powershell\nollama pull phi4-mini\nollama pull llama3.2:3b\n```\n(If `phi4-mini` tag fails, run `ollama list`/`ollama search phi` and use the exact tag shown.)\n\n### Quick reliability test\n```powershell\nollama run phi4-mini \"Return strict JSON only: {\\\"topic\\\":\\\"healthcare staffing\\\",\\\"claim\\\":\\\"Reactive hiring increases total cost\\\",\\\"risk\\\":\\\"turnover and vacancy drag margins\\\"}\"\nollama run llama3.2:3b \"Return strict JSON only: {\\\"topic\\\":\\\"healthcare staffing\\\",\\\"claim\\\":\\\"Reactive hiring increases total cost\\\",\\\"risk\\\":\\\"turnover and vacancy drag margins\\\"}\"\n```\n\nPick whichever gives you:\n1) faster response  \n2) strict JSON compliance  \n3) lower RAM pressure\n\nIf you want, after your test I’ll give you the exact OpenClaw switch command for the winner.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba95e43280819b828ff45925cf198e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":36621,"output":404,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39585,"cost":{"input":0.06408675,"output":0.005656,"cacheRead":0.000448,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.07019075}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773835728976}}
