osoft’s “textbook-quality + reasoning” claim for Phi may be directionally true — but that’s **model training quality**, not guaranteed runtime behavior in *your* stack.\n\nFor you, the truth test is practical:\n1) latency in your environment  \n2) strict JSON reliability  \n3) RAM behavior under agent context  \n\nIf Phi-4-mini wins those, use it. If not, marketing claims don’t matter.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba96a031cc819b835d8c636a6d8f6c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":547,"output":211,"cacheRead":39040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39798,"cost":{"input":0.00095725,"output":0.002954,"cacheRead":0.0068319999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01074325}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773835924954}}
