{"type":"message","id":"355fc6a8","parentId":"85c641c4","timestamp":"2026-03-18T12:13:29.578Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfect. Use these in **PowerShell**:\n\n```powershell\n# 1) Install\nollama pull llama3.2:3b\n\n# 2) Quick response test\nollama run llama3.2:3b \"Rewrite in a concise executive tone: Reactive hiring is expensive because vacancies and bad fit turnover create hidden downstream costs.\"\n\n# 3) JSON reliability test\nollama run llama3.2:3b \"Return strict JSON only: {\\\"topic\\\":\\\"healthcare staffing\\\",\\\"claim\\\":\\\"Reactive hiring increases total cost\\\",\\\"risk\\\":\\\"turnover and vacancy drag margins\\\"}\"\n\n# 4) Check if model is loaded/running\nollama ps\n```\n\nThen in **WSL/OpenClaw** (or tell me to do it), switch model:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw models set ollama/llama3.2:3b\nopenclaw models status --plain\n```\n\nIf `openclaw models set` says unknown model, send me the exact error and I’ll give you the one-line fix.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba96e5b800819bbcb3b1a40c479291\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":430,"output":226,"cacheRead":39424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40080,"cost":{"input":0.0007525,"output":0.003164,"cacheRead":0.006899199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0108157}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773836003750}}
