ersation. Keep responses short and friendly. If there's a new message, send a system event back to the main session with a brief summary.\\\\nCurrent time: Tuesday, March 17th, 2026 — 10:58 AM (Africa/Johannesburg) / 2026-03-17 08:58 UTC\\\\n\\\\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself.\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773737915063\\n        },\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\",\\n              \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Planning WhatsApp session checks**\\\"\\n            },\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\",\\n              \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_VDrPpaLZbREnIXaUmvyc8ykc|fc_0035dc09c146a5a60169b917c2e3cc8191b628dc20b9626c3a\\\",\\n              \\\"name\\\": \\\"sessions_list\\\",\\n              \\\"arguments\\\": {\\n                \\\"limit\\\": 50,\\n                \\\"messageLimit\\\": 5\\n              },\\n              \\\"partialJson\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"limit\\\\\\\":50,\\\\\\\"messageLimit\\\\\\\":5}\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-codex-responses\\\",\\n          \\\"provider\\\": \\\"openai-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"toolUse\\\",\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773737915064\\n        }\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"key\\\": \\\"agent:main:main\\\",\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"other\\\",\\n      \\\"channel\\\": \\\"webchat\\\",\\n      \\\"displayName\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n      \\\"deliveryContext\\\": {\\n        \\\"channel\\\": \\\"webchat\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"updatedAt\\\": 1773737605704,\\n      \\\"sessionId\\\": \\\"7e318110-9c94-4fc1-9fad-509910cfa25e\\\",\\n      \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n      \\\"contextTokens\\\": 272000,\\n      \\\"totalTokens\\\": 131568,\\n      \\\"systemSent\\\": true,\\n      \\\"abortedLastRun\\\": false,\\n      \\\"lastChannel\\\": \\\"webchat\\\",\\n      \\\"transcriptPath\\\": \\\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/7e318110-9c94-4fc1-9fad-509910cfa25e.jsonl\\\",\\n      \\\"messages\\\": [\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\",\\n              \\\"text\\\": \\\" Great question.\\\\n\\\\n`AGENTS.md` is basically your **operating playbook** for me in this workspace.\\\\n\\\\n## What it is\\\\nA persistent instruction layer that defines:\\\\n- how I should start each session,\\\\n- how I should store/maintain memory,\\\\n- what boundaries to respect,\\\\n- how proactive I should be,\\\\n- how to behave in group chats,\\\\n- how to run heartbeat routines, etc.\\\\n\\\\nThink: **“how Dawn works here”**, not “how OpenClaw works globally.”\\\\n\\\\n## True potential uses (where it becomes powerful)\\\\n1) **Codify your standards**\\\\n- response style,\\\\n- decision rules,\\\\n- how much pushback you want,\\\\n- escalation/approval thresholds.\\\\n\\\\n2) **Build repeatable workflows**\\\\n- e.g., Nava content pipeline steps,\\\\n- weekly review rituals,\\\\n- project handoff templates.\\\\n\\\\n3) **Prevent regressions**\\\\n- when I drift or mess up, add a rule once so future sessions improve automatically.\\\\n\\\\n4) **Delegate safely**\\\\n- define what I can do without asking vs what always needs approval.\\\\n\\\\n5) **Multi-project mode switching**\\\\n- separate instructions for Nava vs AbroadWorks so contexts don’t bleed.\\\\n\\\\n6) **Self-improvement system**\\\\n- your new micro/daily/weekly loop belongs here (and now does).\\\\n\\\\n## Practical framing\\\\n- `SOUL.md` = personality/values\\\\n- `AGENTS.md` = execution system\\\\n- `MEMORY.md` = long-term facts about you/work\\\\n- `STATUS.md` = quick current state snapshot\\\\n\\\\nIf you want, next I can propose an **AGENTS v2 structure** specifically for “digital twin across multiple businesses.”\\\",\\n              \\\"textSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"v\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"msg_06b4d78abe8a4afb0169b91539d24c8191bb29c1723f5af511\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"phase\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"final_answer\\\\\\\"}\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-codex-responses\\\",\\n          \\\"provider\\\": \\\"openai-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"stop\\\",\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773737264772\\n        },\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\",\\n              \\\"text\\\": \\\"You could, is it necessary to do right now or can we do this later. Again, just because I'm feeling a bit lazy now and I want to move on to the next thing I want to do, you should push back when necessary and prioritise systems that are better for the long run. Perhaps I should even have you look up the best practices now?\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773737400916,\\n          \\\"senderLabel\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\"\\n        },\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\",\\n              \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Recommending minimal now, rest later**\\\"\\n            },\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\",\\n              \\\"text\\\": \\\" Good self-callout. Pushback: **not necessary right now** to do AGENTS v2 before your next task.\\\\n\\\\nBest long-run move:\\\\n- **Now:** keep momentum, continue your current project.\\\\n- **Later today (scheduled):** run a focused OpenClaw best-practices pass, then do AGENTS v2 once with clean decisions.\\\\n\\\\nYou already have a reminder at **18:30** for best practices, so we’re covered.\\\\n\\\\nIf you want, we move on now — what’s next?\\\",\\n              \\\"textSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"v\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"msg_06b4d78abe8a4afb0169b915c0c7348191b897161c87a17f53\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"phase\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"final_answer\\\\\\\"}\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-codex-responses\\\",\\n          \\\"provider\\\": \\\"openai-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"stop\\\",\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773737400923\\n        },\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\",\\n              \\\"text\\\": \\\"This task I think is best done using your WSL browser. I am not even sure how long it will take but I think there are documents I can look up to help you with this mission. I want you to research Nava Healthcare (NavaHC.com) and read all my articles so that you fully understand the business and the role that I play. It may also be useful to read my LinkedIn and the Nava LinkedIn page to see how I changed my posts. If you go on LinkedIn, be sure to only pay attention to posts made after Aug 2025. Is this a realistic task and should I look up the documents I think will be useful?\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773737597837,\\n          \\\"senderLabel\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\"\\n        },\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\",\\n              \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Advising documentation use**\\\"\\n            },\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\",\\n              \\\"text\\\": \\\" Yes — realistic, and yes, please fetch those docs. That will make the output much better and faster.\\\\n\\\\nBest order (strong recommendation):\\\\n1. **Docs first** (content bible, roadmap, case studies, any internal notes)  \\\\n2. **Nava blog deep read** (your bylined articles first)  \\\\n3. **LinkedIn validation pass** (Nava + your profile, posts after Aug 2025 only)\\\\n\\\\nWhy this order:\\\\n- Docs/blog give the core thinking model.\\\\n- LinkedIn then shows execution evolution.\\\\n- We avoid wasting time scraping before we know what to look for.\\\\n\\\\nIf you want, I’ll run this as a structured research sprint and deliver:\\\\n- your role in Nava (operator map),\\\\n- business model summary,\\\\n- messaging pillars,\\\\n- post-evolution analysis (Aug 2025+),\\\\n- “what to keep / what to stop / what to test next.”\\\",\\n              \\\"textSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"v\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"msg_06b4d78abe8a4afb0169b9168337988191af1975a91834a2d8\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"phase\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"final_answer\\\\\\\"}\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-codex-responses\\\",\\n          \\\"provider\\\": \\\"openai-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"stop\\\",\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773737597842\\n        }\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"key\\\": \\\"agent:main:whatsapp:group:120363416983333048@g.us\\\",\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"group\\\",\\n      \\\"channel\\\": \\\"whatsapp\\\",\\n      \\\"displayName\\\": \\\"whatsapp:g-social-media-post\\\",\\n      \\\"deliveryContext\\\": {\\n        \\\"channel\\\": \\\"whatsapp\\\",\\n        \\\"to\\\": \\\"120363416983333048@g.us\\\",\\n        \\\"accountId\\\": \\\"default\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"updatedAt\\\": 1773125733430,\\n      \\\"sessionId\\\": \\\"6b68e9f0-54ec-43f3-98fb-178d333036ca\\\",\\n      \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n      \\\"lastChannel\\\": \\\"whatsapp\\\",\\n      \\\"lastTo\\\": \\\"120363416983333048@g.us\\\",\\n      \\\"l