{"type":"message","id":"8a1f40b2","parentId":"e1c516ea","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:24:34.125Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Fresh session ready.**\n\nCurrent state:\n- **Model:** `ollama/minimax-m2.5:cloud` (still active from before reset)\n- **Memory:** Still broken (`Provider: none`, `0/6 files`)\n\nThe issue: Memory indexing needs an **embedding provider** (like OpenAI text-embedding-3-small), but you only have **chat model OAuth** (OpenAI Codex). They're different services.\n\nOptions:\n1. **Update OpenClaw** to 2026.3.13 (may have fixes) — earlier network attempt failed, can retry\n2. **Configure embedding provider** — add an API key for embeddings (Voyage, Mistral, or OpenAI embeddings)\n3. **Keep FTS-only mode** — works for keyword search, just no semantic similarity\n\nWant me to:\n- Try the update again?\n- Configure an embedding provider (I'd need an API key)?\n- Or proceed with other tasks while keeping FTS-only for now?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":37085,"output":440,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37525,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773854674120}}
{"type":"message","id":"0df10c6c","parentId":"8a1f40b2","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:26:15.901Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-18 19:23:58 GMT+2] Exec completed (fresh-em, code 0) :: OpenClaw 2026.3.8 (3caab92) null null\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-03-18 19:26 GMT+2] What do you mean the OpenClaw update \"may have fixes\"? Also, I don't know what you mean by embedding a provider?"}],"timestamp":1773854775897}}
{"type":"message","id":"1820cc60","parentId":"0df10c6c","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:26:28.987Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fair questions — let me clarify:\n\n### 1. \"May have fixes\"\nOpenClaw 2026.3.13 is newer than your 2026.3.8. Newer versions often include bug fixes. I'm not *certain* it fixes memory, but it's worth trying since we're stuck.\n\n### 2. \"Embedding provider\"\nTwo types of search:\n- **Keyword search (FTS):** Finds exact words you type. If you search \"payment problem\" it only finds \"payment problem\" — not synonyms like \"billing issue\" or \"late fee\"\n- **Semantic search:** Converts text to mathematical vectors, finds meaning similarity. \"Payment problem\" would also match \"billing issue\" or \"late fee\"\n\n**Embedding = the math that converts text to vectors.**\n\nYour current setup:\n- ✅ Chat works (uses GPT models via OAuth)\n- ✅ Keyword search works (FTS)\n- ❌ Semantic search broken (no embedding provider configured)\n\nTo fix semantic memory, you'd need:\n- An **embedding model** (like OpenAI's `text-embedding-3-small`, or free alternatives like Voyage)\n- An **API key** for that service\n\nWithout it, you're stuck with keyword-only search.\n\n**Simpler path:** Just use keyword search (FTS) — it's already working. The \"semantic\" part is nice-to-have, not essential.\n\nWant me to try the OpenClaw update first, or just proceed with what works?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":37444,"output":579,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38023,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773854788986}}
