{"type":"message","id":"e746890d","parentId":"55af6e2d","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:54:18.054Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — Ollama has a **cloud service** where models run on remote GPUs. \n\nThe `nemotron-3-super` in their library is likely accessible via cloud. To use it:\n\n```bash\nollama run nemotron-3-super\n```\n\nThis will either:\n- Run it on your local machine if you have it downloaded, OR\n- Use Ollama's cloud infrastructure (remote GPUs) if available\n\nThe API response showed it's in Ollama's library — so yes, it's accessible. You'll just need to check if your Ollama account has cloud access enabled, or if it's pay-per-use.\n\n**To verify it's working:**\n```bash\nollama list\n```\n\nOr just try:\n```bash\nollama run nemotron-3-super \"Hello\"\n```\n\nThat should either pull/run locally or route to cloud automatically. Want me to help you test it?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":45592,"output":409,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46001,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773856458053}}
