{"type":"message","id":"caf0a17e","parentId":"e69df715","timestamp":"2026-03-18T18:07:37.452Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That's the right API call. To make it work with Ollama Cloud:\n\n**1. Set your API key first (in WSL):**\n\n```bash\nexport OLLAMA_API_KEY=\"your-key-here\"\n```\n\n**2. Then run the curl:**\n\n```bash\ncurl http://localhost:11434/api/chat \\\n  -d '{\n    \"model\": \"nemotron-3-super\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello!\"}]\n  }'\n```\n\nThe key tells Ollama to route to their cloud servers instead of local.\n\n**Alternative:** You might need to specify the cloud model explicitly. Try:\n\n```bash\nollama run nemotron-3-super \"Hello\"\n```\n\nThat should auto-handle the auth. Did you set the env var? Let me know what happens when you try it."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":49795,"output":270,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50065,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773857257452}}
