{"type":"compaction","id":"e763a1e3","parentId":"be354f2a","timestamp":"2026-03-18T18:45:16.710Z","summary":"## Decisions\n- **Local-first LLM strategy**: Default to local Ollama for routine content tasks (summarization, rewrite, formatting, schema filling), escalate to ChatGPT only for hard reasoning, ambiguous strategy, or high-stakes final drafting\n- **Qwen3:4b-instruct selected**: Best balance of quality/speed for 16GB laptop, ~2.5-4.5GB download size, 4-8GB RAM runtime\n- **Guardrails enforced**: RAG-only evidence mode, domain gate (Nava staffing/recruiting only), confidence gate (\"insufficient support\" when weak), human approval before publish\n- **WSL memory boost applied**: Increased WSL visible RAM from ~7.6GB to ~11GB via .wslconfig updates\n- **Skill install deferral**: Keep installs minimal during content-production day; prioritize workflow artifacts over tooling sprawl\n- **Local models abandoned for now**: After 8-minute response times and crashes with Llama 3.2:3b, user decided local models not worth it on current hardware - switched to OpenAI-only\n- **Llama 3.2:3b tested**: JSON schema reliability poor (mutated keys/values), prose rewrite acceptable but not reliable for strict JSON tasks\n- **Change-control rule**: Assistant must provide read-only diagnosis first, ask for approval before applying config changes\n- **Nava Mode concept**: Proposed project-specific persona overlay with domain restrictions, separate from core assistant - activated via \"Enter Nava Mode\" / \"Exit Nava Mode\"\n- **Session reset executed**: User initiated context reset to test new Ollama context settings; memories persisted; new session will resume memory repair thread\n\n## Open TODOs\n1. ~~Complete Task 1: Skill/tool research + setup~~ - DONE (local model experiments completed, reverted to OpenAI)\n2. ~~Verify Qwen3:4b-instruct works locally~~ - DONE (worked but too slow in OpenClaw context)\n3. ~~Lock exact local model routing policy~~ - DONE (local abandoned, OpenAI-only)\n4. Task 2: Content engine spec finalization\n5. Task 3: Ingestion update flow for new articles\n6. Task 4: Generate idea bank from corpus\n7. Task 5: Draft queue-ready posts for LinkedIn/X/FB\n8. Task 6: Image refinement workflow\n9. Task 7: Final queue pack + ordering\n10. Fix memory retrieval (provider: none, mode: fts-only) - read-only diagnostic complete, awaiting next session to implement fix\n11. **SESSION RESET COMPLETE**: Memories saved, next session resumes memory repair\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Quality over speed: \"I don't want guaranteed delivery, I want this done properly\"\n- Must warn before any high-token GPT steps\n- Must map every idea to Nava staffing/recruiting taxonomy with source evidence URLs\n- Must reject non-Nava-domain content\n- Human review required before any publish\n- **NEW**: No silent config mutations - diagnosis first, approval before changes\n- **NEW**: Mode-switching framework for project-specific behavior (Nava Mode vs core Dawn)\n- Session reset clears accumulated context; new session starts fresh with loaded memories\n\n## Pending user asks\n1. ~~Qwen download issue~~ - RESOLVED (installed and tested)\n2. ~~Model reliability test~~ - RESOLVED (Llama tested, JSON unreliable)\n3. ~~Local model benchmarking~~ - RESOLVED (abandoned due to 8-min latency + crash)\n4. ~~Google Docs + Gemini integration~~ - DEFERRED to later phase\n5. ~~Image refinement process~~ - DEFERRED to Task 6\n6. **Memory retrieval fix**: User asked \"Do you know how to fix it?\" - assistant offered read-only diagnostics, awaiting user \"go\" in next session\n7. **Task 2-7 execution**: User wants to skip local-model tasks and proceed to content engine work - assistant ready to start in next session\n8. **Session reset hand-off**: Complete - new session will auto-load memory files\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- Cron job (WhatsApp check, now disabled): `a17613ed-5c6e-46a8-aff9-d010ceb706b0`\n- Cron job (sprint check-in, 30min): `fe4180d9-037f-413a-a1dd-c7