ause the embedding provider is still broken (FTS-only mode). Let me read the memory files directly to get context.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): # 2026-03-18\n\n## Notes\n\n- User successfully installed and tested `qwen3:4b-instruct` locally via Ollama (rewrite + strict JSON checks passed).\n- Observed that leaving Qwen loaded can consume high RAM (~13 GB resident); stopping model frees memory.\n- Added local-first/fallback docs and scripts:\n  - `OLLAMA_OPENAI_FALLBACK_GUIDE.md`\n  - `scripts/openclaw-model-preflight.ps1`\n  - Windows copy: `%USERPROFILE%\\\\openclaw-model-preflight.ps1`\n- Cross-OS execution issue identified: PowerShell script called `openclaw`, but OpenClaw binary was in WSL path; patched script to route through WSL fallback.\n-...\n- Assistant: Good. I have context. Now let me check model status and memory status to see current state.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): ollama/minimax-m2.5:cloud\nMemory Search (main)\nProvider: none (requested: auto)\nModel: none\nSources: memory\nIndexed: 0/6 files · 0 chunks\nDirty: yes\nStore: ~/.openclaw/memory/main.sqlite\nWorkspace: ~/.openclaw/workspace\nEmbeddings: unavailable\nEmbeddings error: No API key found for provider \"openai\". You are authenticated with OpenAI Codex OAuth. Use openai-codex/gpt-5.4 (OAuth) or set OPENAI_API_KEY to use openai/gpt-5.4.\n\nNo API key found for provider \"google\". Auth store: /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json (agentDir: /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/agent). ...\n- Assistant: Fresh session. Key findings:\n\n- **Model:** `ollama/minimax-m2.5:cloud` (persisted from before)\n- **Memory:** Still broken — `Provider: none`, `0/6 files indexed`\n- **Error:** `\"No API key found for provider 'openai'. You are authenticated with OpenAI Codex OAuth. Use openai-codex/gpt-5.4 (OAuth) or set OPENAI_API_KEY.\"`\n\nThe error message is confusing — it says \"Use openai-codex/gpt-5.4 (OAuth)\" but memory still doesn't work. Let me check the current version vs available updates.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): Command still running (session fresh-ember, pid 10739). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up.\n- Assistant: The command is still running. Let me wait for it to complete.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (process): OpenClaw 2026.3.8 (3caab92)\nnull\nnull\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0.\n- Assistant: The version shows 2026.3.8. The earlier status check showed 2026.3.13 is available. Let me check if there's a newer version that might fix the memory embedding issue. However, earlier I tried to update and it failed due to network issues. Let me try again or check what the actual fix approach should be.\n\nActually, given the user said \"let's start the new session\" and wants me to continue the memory task, I should just proceed with diagnosing and fixing the memory issue. The issue is that:\n\n1. Memory is in FTS-only mode because no embedding provider is configured\n2. The error says to use openai...\n- Tool result (exec): {\n  \"update\": {\n    \"root\": \"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw\",\n    \"installKind\": \"package\",\n    \"packageManager\": \"pnpm\",\n    \"deps\": {\n      \"manager\": \"pnpm\",\n      \"status\": \"unknown\",\n      \"lockfilePath\": \"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/pnpm-lock.yaml\",\n      \"markerPath\": \"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/node_modules/.modules.yaml\",\n      \"reason\": \"lockfile missing\"\n    },\n    \"registry\": {\n      \"latestVersion\": \"2026.3.13\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"channel\": {\n    \"value\": \"stable\",\n    \"source\": \"default\",\n    \"label\": \"stable (...\n- Assistant: **Fresh session ready.**\n\nCurrent state:\n- **Model:** `ollama/minimax-m2.5:cloud` (still active from before reset)\n- **Memory:** Still broken (`Provider: none`, `0/6 files`)\n\nThe issue: Memory indexing needs an **embedding provider** (like OpenAI text-embedding-3-small), but you only have **chat model OAuth** (OpenAI Codex). They're different services.\n\nOptions:\n1. **Update OpenClaw** to 2026.3.13 (may have fixes) — earlier network attempt failed, can retry\n2. **Configure embedding provider** — add an API key for embeddings (Voyage, Mistral, or OpenAI embeddings)\n3. **Keep FTS-only mode** — wo...\n- User: System: [2026-03-18 19:23:58 GMT+2] Exec completed (fresh-em, code 0) :: OpenClaw 2026.3.8 (3caab92) null null\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-03-18 19:26 GMT+2] What do you mean the OpenClaw update \"may have fixes\"? Also, I don't know what you mean by embedding a provider?\n- Assistant: Fair questions — let me clarify:\n\n### 1. \"May have fixes\"\nOpenClaw 2026.3.13 is newer than your 2026.3.8. Newer versions often include bug fixes. I'm not *certain* it fixes memory, but it's worth trying since we're stuck.\n\n### 2. \"Embedding provider\"\nTwo types of search:\n- **Keyword search (FTS):** Finds exact words you type. If you search \"payment problem\" it only finds \"payment problem\" — not synonyms like \"billing issue\" or \"late fee\"\n- **Semantic search:** Converts text to mathematical vectors, finds meaning similarity. \"Payment problem\" would also match \"billing issue\" or \"late fee\"\n\n**Em...\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-18.md\n</modified-files>\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don