OZaz4NMXWT_ifQSJmeZMqxXM_18FY_M8Mb1n_1JDR6FoRvugPAGm4AQcduOrFy1UwUOsnoQiRjV2FgayoQ226pFYIlwccelhHFmZcjKfA9MSiqosfjyP9HxNZKvINdAk90rxxdlHs0Kq3u21K3450fptFzMmrGZIoxr-d53HBUfPDfbErDk3gJ2oqPL6RAgD2qy3cF0PNjZ7xbgFvhYCI4ZrRYyzJQeEYLiymUrcCooT1V9p3AeTcO6Jn-N4MvZCO8725GTBM3jXUo6Y_WRQfRig3k15Bw63wzy9LJw-4lL85s6EVKrVQ=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Starting task file creation**\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_IpKcRYHA4EPVPGh4WTCFz4vm|fc_069f3e295d6234390169bafafd632c8196954179e26293d963","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/TASK2_CONTENT_ENGINE_SPEC.md","content":"# Task 2 — Nava Content Engine Spec (Final Draft v1)\n\nDate: 2026-03-18\nOwner: Dawn\nStatus: Draft ready for user review\n\n## 1) Objective\nCreate a production-safe content engine for Nava that:\n- Generates ideas and drafts only within Nava’s staffing/recruiting domain\n- Grounds claims in source evidence from approved corpus/docs\n- Produces channel-ready outputs (LinkedIn + X mandatory; FB optional)\n- Enforces human review before any publish action\n\n## 2) Non-Negotiable Guardrails\n1. Domain gate: only staffing/recruiting content tied to Nava taxonomy\n2. Evidence gate: claims must map to source URLs or internal doc citations\n3. Confidence gate: if evidence is weak, output `insufficient support`\n4. Publish gate: no autonomous publishing; explicit human approval required\n5. Format gate: channel templates must be followed exactly\n\n## 3) Inputs\n- Website corpus (crawl + clean text + synthesis)\n- Internal docs (`docs/`, `docs/converted/`)\n- RAG index outputs (`rag/index/*`)\n- Existing guardrails config (`rag/config/content_guardrails.yaml`)\n\n## 4) Content Taxonomy (enforced)\nEach idea/draft must tag:\n- Primary topic\n- Audience (candidate / employer / operator)\n- Funnel stage (awareness / consideration / conversion)\n- Evidence set (source ids/urls)\n- Risk level (low/med/high claim sensitivity)\n\nIf taxonomy tag cannot be assigned confidently -> reject item.\n\n## 5) Pipeline\n## Stage A — Idea Generation\nInput: corpus gaps + recent themes\nOutput: structured idea cards with:\n- headline\n- thesis\n- target audience\n- taxonomy tags\n- required evidence checklist\n\n## Stage B — Evidence Binding\nFor each idea:\n- Run retrieval\n- Attach top supporting snippets + URLs\n- Mark unsupported lines\n\nPass criteria: each major claim has at least one explicit source.\n\n## Stage C — Drafting\nGenerate:\n- LinkedIn draft (primary)\n- X derivative (1–3 tweets)\n- Optional FB adaptation only when fit is high\n\nRules:\n- Executive/operator tone\n- Compressed sentences, natural short paragraphs\n- Caption complements image (does not restate)\n\n## Stage D — Validation\nAutomated checks:\n- Domain classifier pass/fail\n- Evidence coverage score\n- Style constraints\n- Banned/off-domain phrase detection\n\nIf fail -> return diagnostics + regenerate.\n\n## Stage E — Human Review Pack\nBundle per post:\n- Final draft(s)\n- Claim-to-source map\n- Risk notes\n- Suggested image direction\n\nNo queue/publish unless approved.\n\n## 6) Output Schemas\n## 6.1 Idea Card\n- id\n- title\n- one_line_angle\n- audience\n- taxonomy_tags[]\n- evidence_requirements[]\n- rejection_reason (nullable)\n\n## 6.2 Draft Pack\n- draft_id\n- channel (linkedin|x|fb)\n- copy\n- claims[]\n- sources[]\n- confidence_score\n- review_status (needs_review|approved|rejected)\n\n## 7) Quality Targets\n- 100% taxonomy-tagged ideas\n- 100% major claims source-linked\n- <5% off-domain rejects after prompt tuning\n- Zero publish without human approval\n\n## 8) Model Routing (current agreed posture)\n- Primary execution: Minimax cloud in OpenClaw session\n- Keep prompts short/structured to reduce context bloat\n- Use strict templates for schema outputs\n\n## 9) Next Deliverables (Task 3+ handoff)\n1. Ingestion update flow for new articles (Task 3)\n2. Corpus-derived idea bank (Task 4)\n3. Queue-ready drafts for LinkedIn/X/FB (Task 5)\n4. Image refinement workflow (Task 6)\n5. Final queue pack + ordering (Task 7)\n\n## 10) Open Decisions for Tiny\n1. Confirm final taxonomy labels (if any rename needed)\n2. Set confidence score threshold for `insufficient support`\n3. Confirm FB inclusion rule (always optional vs conditional)\n4. Confirm claim granularity for source mapping (line-by-line vs grouped)\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/TASK2_CONTENT_ENGINE_SPEC.md\",\"content\":\"# Task 2 — Nava Content Engine Spec (Final Draft v1)\\n\\nDate: 2026-03-18\\nOwner: Dawn\\nStatus: Draft ready for user review\\n\\n## 1) Objective\\nCreate a production-safe content engine for Nava that:\\n- Generates ideas and drafts only within Nava’s staffing/recruiting domain\\n- Grounds claims in source evidence from approved corpus/docs\\n- Produces channel-ready outputs (LinkedIn + X mandatory; FB optional)\\n- Enforces human review before any publish action\\n\\n## 2) Non-Negotiable Guardrails\\n1. Domain gate: only staffing/recruiting content tied to Nava taxonomy\\n2. Evidence gate: claims must map to source URLs or internal doc citations\\n3. Confidence gate: if evidence is weak, output `insufficient support`\\n4. Publish gate: no autonomous publishing; explicit human approval required\\n5. Format gate: channel templates must be followed exactly\\n\\n## 3) Inputs\\n- Website corpus (crawl + clean text + synthesis)\\n- Internal docs (`docs/`, `docs/converted/`)\\n- RAG index outputs (`rag/index/*`)\\n- Existing guardrails config (`rag/config/content_guardrails.yaml`)\\n\\n## 4) Content Taxonomy (enforced)\\nEach idea/draft must tag:\\n- Primary topic\\n- Audience (candidate / employer / operator)\\n- Funnel stage (awareness / consideration / conversion)\\n- Evidence set (source ids/urls)\\n- Risk level (low/med/high claim sensitivity)\\n\\nIf taxonomy tag cannot be assigned confidently -> reject item.\\n\\n## 5) Pipeline\\n## Stage A — Idea Generation\\nInput: corpus gaps + recent themes\\nOutput: structured idea cards with:\\n- headline\\n- thesis\\n- target audience\\n- taxonomy tags\\n- required evidence checklist\\n\\n## Stage B — Evidence Binding\\nFor each idea:\\n- Run retrieval\\n- Attach top supporting snippets + URLs\\n- Mark unsupported lines\\n\\nPass criteria: each major claim has at least one explicit source.\\n\\n## Stage C — Drafting\\nGenerate:\\n- LinkedIn draft (primary)\\n- X derivative (1–3 tweets)\\n- Optional FB adaptation only when fit is high\\n\\nRules:\\n- Executive/operator tone\\n- Compressed sentences, natural short paragraphs\\n- Caption complements image (does not restate)\\n\\n## Stage D — Validation\\nAutomated checks:\\n- Domain classifier pass/fail\\n- Evidence coverage score\\n- Style constraints\\n- Banned/off-domain phrase detection\\n\\nIf fail -> return diagnostics + regenerate.\\n\\n## Stage E — Human Review Pack\\nBundle per post:\\n- Final draft(s)\\n- Claim-to-source map\\n- Risk notes\\n- Suggested image direction\\n\\nNo queue/publish unless approved.\\n\\n## 6) Output Schemas\\n## 6.1 Idea Card\\n- id\\n- title\\n- one_line_angle\\n- audience\\n- taxonomy_tags[]\\n- evidence_requirements[]\\n- rejection_reason (nullable)\\n\\n## 6.2 Draft Pack\\n- draft_id\\n- channel (linkedin|x|fb)\\n- copy\\n- claims[]\\n- sources[]\\n- confidence_score\\n- review_status (needs_review|approved|rejected)\\n\\n## 7) Quality Targets\\n- 100% taxonomy-tagged ideas\\n- 100% major claims source-linked\\n- <5% off-domain rejects after prompt tuning\\n- Zero publish without human approval\\n\\n## 8) Model Routing (current agreed posture)\\n- Primary execution: Minimax cloud in OpenClaw session\\n- Keep prompts short/structured to reduce context bloat\\n- Use strict templates for schema outputs\\n\\n## 9) Next Deliverables (Task 3+ handoff)\\n1. Ingestion update flow for new articles (Task 3)\\n2. Corpus-derived idea bank (Task 4)\\n3. Queue-ready drafts for LinkedIn/X/FB (Task 5)\\n4. Image refinement workflow (Task 6)\\n5. Final queue pack + ordering (Task 7)\\n\\n## 10) Open Decisions for Tiny\\n1. Confirm final taxonomy labels (if any rename needed)\\n2. Set confidence score threshold for `insufficient support`\\n3. Confirm FB inclusion rule (always optional vs conditional)\\n4. Confirm claim granularity for source mapping (line-by-line vs grouped)\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":93699,"output":1141,"cacheRead":46464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141304,"cost":{"input":0.16397325,"output":0.015974,"cacheRead":0.0081312,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.18807844999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773861612991}}
